Brazilian Stock Movers: LLX Logistica, Petrobras, Pao de Acucar

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-04-12T20:48:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/brazilian-stock-movers-pao-de-acucar-petrobras-usiminas-vale.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index fell 1.9 percent to 66,896.23.  LLX Logistica SA (LLXL3)  (LLXL3 BS), the construction and logistics
company owned by billionaire  Eike Batista , declined 3.9 percent
to 4.95 reais as the IMF and the  International Energy Agency 
said that crude prices above $100 a barrel are starting to hurt
the global economy. Oil posted its biggest two-day drop in
almost 11 months, falling 3.3 percent to $106.25 a barrel.  PortX
Operacoes Portuarias SA (PRTX3)  (PRTX3 BS), a Brazilian port operator,
dropped 3.3 percent to 3.77 reais.  Cia. Brasileira de Distribuicao Grupo Pao de Acucar (PCAR4
BS) dropped 1.4 percent to 65.35 reais as the national
statistics agency said Brazil’s retail sales fell 0.4 percent in
February, the first monthly decline in a year. The median
estimate of 30 analysts surveyed by Bloomberg called for sales
to be unchanged in February.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)  (PETR4 BS), Brazil’s state-
controlled oil company, dropped 3.1 percent to 26.65 reais as
crude tumbled amid investor concern that government caps on
domestic gasoline prices will curb profit. Petrobras sells
gasoline at about a 16 percent discount to international prices,
said Lucas Brendler, a  fund manager  at Banco Geracao Futuro de
Investimentos in  Porto Alegre .  Vale SA (VALE3)  (VALE5 BS), the world’s second-largest miner,
retreated 1.9 percent to 46.43 reais as copper declined for a
second day in New York on speculation investors may avoid
riskier assets after  Japan  raised the severity rating of its
nuclear crisis to the highest level.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in  New York  
